  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="what-is" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">What Is Royalty-Free Music?</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Royalty-free music is music that you can use without paying ongoing royalties to the copyright holder. Contrary to popular belief, "royalty-free" doesn't mean "free" or "no copyright" - it means you pay once (or get a license) and can use the music without additional per-use fees.</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">What Royalty-Free IS:</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Music you can use after obtaining a license</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">No ongoing per-use or per-view payments</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Typically available for a one-time fee or subscription</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Can be used in multiple projects (depending on license)</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">What Royalty-Free IS NOT:</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Automatically free to use without permission</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Public domain (though some can be)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Free from copyright protection</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Usable without reading the license terms</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="licenses" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Types of Music Licenses Explained</h2>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">1. Royalty-Free License</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Pay once, use multiple times. This is what most content creators need.</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">2. Creative Commons Licenses</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong>CC0:</strong> Public domain, use anywhere for anything, no attribution needed</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong>CC BY:</strong> Free to use, attribution required</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>CC BY-NC:</strong> Free for non-commercial use only, attribution required</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">3. Exclusive License</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">You're the only person who can use the music. Expensive but gives you unique audio.</p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="youtube" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Royalty-Free Music for YouTube</h2>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Content ID Claims vs Copyright Strikes</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong>Content ID claim:</strong> Your video is flagged, revenue goes to music owner, video stays up</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>Copyright strike:</strong> Video taken down, strike on your channel, 3 strikes = channel termination</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Best Practices for YouTube</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Only use music you have explicit permission to use</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Keep license documentation for disputes</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Read "monetization" terms carefully</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

